All accessibility improvements are complete. Here's a summary of changes:

### Files modified:

**`components/SkipLink.tsx`** (new) — Skip-to-content link, visible only on focus

**`app/page.tsx`** — Added `<SkipLink />` before navigation, added `id="main-content"` to `<main>`

**`app/globals.css`** — Three additions:
- `.skip-link` styles (hidden by default, slides in on `:focus`)
- `*:focus-visible` outline with `var(--accent)` color and 2px offset
- `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — disables all animations and transitions

**`app/globals.css`** — Contrast fix: bumped `--text-tertiary` alpha from 0.4→0.55 (dark) and 0.5→0.64 (light) across all three theme blocks (`:root`, `.dark`, `.light`, system fallback) to meet WCAG 4.5:1

**`components/Navigation.tsx`** — Added `aria-label` to language toggle button

**`context/LanguageContext.tsx`** — Syncs `document.documentElement.lang` to `pt-BR`/`en` when language changes

### Already in good shape (no changes needed):
- `lang="pt-BR"` already on `<html>`
- Heading hierarchy: exactly one `<h1>`, proper h2→h3→h4→h5 nesting
- Icon-only buttons (theme toggle, hamburger, AI chat open/close/send) already had `aria-label`

